g1003.definition: [Βοόζ] of Hebrew origin ({{h1162}}); Booz, (i.e. Boaz), an Israelite

g1005.definition: [βοῤῥᾶς] of uncertain derivation; the north (properly, wind)

g1006.definition: [βόσκω] a prolonged form of a primary verb (compare {{g977}}, {{g1016}}); to pasture; by extension to, fodder; reflexively, to graze

g1007.definition: [Βοσόρ] of Hebrew origin ({{h1160}}); Bosor (i.e. Beor), a Moabite

g1009.definition: [βότρυς] of uncertain derivation; a bunch (of grapes)

g1010.definition: [βουλευτής] from {{g1011}}; an adviser, i.e. (specially) a councillor or member of the Jewish Sanhedrin

g1011.definition: [βουλεύω] from {{g1012}}; to advise, i.e. (reflexively) deliberate, or (by implication) resolve

g1012.definition: [βουλή] from {{g1014}}; volition, i.e. (objectively) advice, or (by implication) purpose

g1014.definition: [βούλομαι] middle voice of a primary verb; to "will," i.e. (reflexively) be willing Compare {{g2309}}.

g1015.definition: [βουνός] probably of foreign origin; a hillock

g1016.definition: [βοῦς] probably from the base of {{g1006}}; an ox (as grazing), i.e. an animal of that species ("beef")

g1017.definition: [βραβεῖον] from βραβεύς (an umpire of uncertain derivation); an award (of arbitration), i.e. (specially) a prize in the public games

g1018.definition: [βραβεύω] from the same as {{g1017}}; to arbitrate, i.e. (genitive case) to govern (figuratively, prevail)

g1020.definition: [βραδυπλοέω] from {{g1021}} and a prolonged form of {{g4126}}; to sail slowly

g1021.definition: [βραδύς] of uncertain affinity; slow; figuratively, dull

g1023.definition: [βραχίων] properly, comparative of {{g1024}}, but apparently in the sense of βράσσω (to wield); the arm, i.e. (figuratively) strength

g1024.definition: [βραχύς] of uncertain affinity; short (of time, place, quantity, or number)

g1025.definition: [βρέφος] of uncertain affinity; an infant (properly, unborn) literally or figuratively

g1026.definition: [βρέχω] a primary verb; to moisten (especially by a shower)

g1031.definition: [βρύχω] a primary verb; to grate the teeth (in pain or rage)

g1032.definition: [βρύω] a primary verb; to swell out, i.e. (by implication) to gush

g1033.definition: [βρῶμα] from the base of {{g977}}; food (literally or figuratively), especially (ceremonially) articles allowed or forbidden by the Jewish law

g1035.definition: [βρῶσις] from the base of {{g977}}; (abstractly) eating (literally or figuratively); by extension (concretely) food (literally or figuratively)

g1036.definition: [βυθίζω] from {{g1037}}; to sink; by implication, to drown

g1037.definition: [βυθός] a variation of {{g899}}; depth, i.e. (by implication) the sea

g1039.definition: [βύσσινος] from {{g1040}}; made of linen (neuter a linen cloth)

g1041.definition: [βωμός] from the base of {{g939}}; properly, a stand, i.e. (specially) an altar

g1042.definition: [γαββαθά] of Chaldee origin (compare {{h1355}}); the knoll; gabbatha, a vernacular term for the Roman tribunal in Jerusalem

g1043.definition: [Γαβριήλ] of Hebrew origin ({{h1403}}); Gabriel, an archangel

g1045.definition: [Γάδ] of Hebrew origin ({{h1410}}); Gad, a tribe of Israelites

g1046.definition: [Γαδαρηνός] from Γαδαρά (a town east of the Jordan); a Gadarene or inhabitant of Gadara

g1048.definition: [Γάζα] of Hebrew origin ({{h5804}}); Gazah (i.e. Azzah), a place in Palestine

g1049.definition: [γαζοφυλάκιον] from {{g1047}} and {{g5438}}; a treasure-house, i.e. a court in the temple for the collection-boxes

g1050.definition: [Γάϊος] of Latin origin; Gaius (i.e. Caius), a Christian

g1052.definition: [Γαλάτης] from {{g1053}}; a Galatian or inhabitant of Galatia

g1053.definition: [Γαλατία] of foreign origin; Galatia, a region of Asia

g1054.definition: [Γαλατικός] from {{g1053}}; Galatic or relating to Galatia

g1056.definition: [Γαλιλαία] of Hebrew origin ({{h1551}}); Galilæa (i.e. the heathen circle), a region of Palestine

g1057.definition: [Γαλιλαῖος] from {{g1056}}; Galilean or belonging to Galilea

g1058.definition: [Γαλλίων] of Latin origin; Gallion (i.e. Gallio), a Roman officer

g1059.definition: [Γαμαλιήλ] of Hebrew origin ({{h1583}}); Gamaliel (i.e. Gamliel), an Israelite

g1061.definition: [γαμίσκω] from {{g1062}}; to espouse (a daughter to a husband)

g1063.definition: [γάρ] a primary particle; properly, assigning a reason (used in argument, explanation or intensification; often with other particles)

g1064.definition: [γαστήρ] of uncertain derivation; the stomach; by analogy, the matrix; figuratively, a gourmand

g1065.definition: [γέ] a primary particle of emphasis or qualification (often used with other particles prefixed)

g1066.definition: [Γεδεών] of Hebrew origin ({{h1439}}); Gedeon (i.e. Gid(e)on), an Israelite

g1067.definition: [γέεννα] of Hebrew origin ({{h1516}} and {{h2011}}); valley of (the son of) Hinnom; ge-henna (or Ge-Hinnom), a valley of Jerusalem, used (figuratively) as a name for the place (or state) of everlasting punishment

g1068.definition: [Γεθσημανῆ] of Chaldee origin (compare {{h1660}} and {{h8081}}); oil-press; Gethsemane, a garden near Jerusalem

g1069.definition: [γείτων] from {{g1093}}; a neighbour (as adjoining one's ground); by implication, a friend

g1070.definition: [γελάω] of uncertain affinity; to laugh (as a sign of joy or satisfaction)

g1071.definition: [γέλως] from {{g1070}}; laughter (as a mark of gratification)

g1073.definition: [γέμω] a primary verb; to swell out, i.e. be full

g1074.definition: [γενεά] from (a presumed derivative of) {{g1085}}; a generation; by implication, an age (the period or the persons)

g1075.definition: [γενεαλογέω] from {{g1074}} and {{g3056}}; to reckon by generations, i.e. trace in genealogy

g1076.definition: [γενεαλογία] from the same as {{g1075}}; tracing by generations, i.e. "genealogy"

g1077.definition: [γενέσια] neuter plural of a derivative of {{g1078}}; birthday ceremonies

g1078.definition: [γένεσις] from the same as {{g1074}}; nativity; figuratively, nature

g1079.definition: [γενετή] feminine of a presumed derivative of the base of {{g1074}}; birth

g1080.definition: [γεννάω] from a variation of {{g1085}}; to procreate (properly, of the father, but by extension of the mother); figuratively, to regenerate

g1081.definition: [γέννημα] from {{g1080}}; offspring; by analogy, produce (literally or figuratively)

g1082.definition: [Γεννησαρέτ] of Hebrew origin (compare {{h3672}}); Gennesaret (i.e. Kinnereth), a lake and plain in Palestine

g1085.definition: [γένος] from {{g1096}}; "kin" (abstract or concrete, literal or figurative, individual or collective)

g1086.definition: [Γεργεσηνός] of Hebrew origin ({{h1622}}); a Gergesene (i.e. Girgashite) or one of the aborigines of Palestine

g1087.definition: [γερουσία] from {{g1088}}; the eldership, i.e. (collectively) the Jewish Sanhedrin

g1089.definition: [γεύομαι] a primary verb; to taste; by implication, to eat; figuratively, to experience (good or ill)

g1091.definition: [γεώργιον] neuter of a (presumed) derivative of {{g1092}}; cultivable, i.e. a farm

g1092.definition: [γεωργός] from {{g1093}} and the base of {{g2041}}; a land-worker, i.e. farmer

g1093.definition: [γῆ] contracted from a primary word; soil; by extension a region, or the solid part or the whole of the terrene globe (including the occupants in each application)

g1096.definition: [γίνομαι] a prolongation and middle voice form of a primary verb; to cause to be ("gen"-erate), i.e. (reflexively) to become (come into being), used with great latitude (literal, figurative, intensive, etc.)

g1097.definition: [γινώσκω] a prolonged form of a primary verb; to "know" (absolutely) in a great variety of applications and with many implications (as follow, with others not thus clearly expressed)

g1098.definition: [γλεῦκος] akin to {{g1099}}; sweet wine, i.e. (properly) must (fresh juice), but used of the more saccharine (and therefore highly inebriating) fermented wine

g1099.definition: [γλυκύς] of uncertain affinity; sweet (i.e. not bitter nor salt)

g1100.definition: [γλῶσσα] of uncertain affinity; the tongue; by implication, a language (specially, one naturally unacquired)
